{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:23:55.404Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Assessing Premium Security**\n\nI'm currently focused on the security guard component, which appears to offer a premium experience. The key features that I have noted are beautiful live terminal logs that update at regular intervals, and comprehensive support for selecting simulated roles such as client_admin, client_member, and gff. I am very impressed by the comprehensive design.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:23:56.504Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Confirming System Integrity**\n\nI've just finished verifying the system's integrity according to the Phase 4 QA requirements. The good news is that no files were changed during the final checks, indicating a clean state. I ran `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, `npm run typecheck`, and `npm test`, all of which passed without any reported warnings or errors. This is ideal! Now, I am constructing the final checklist and summary to pass on.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
